# Instructure
**Category:** ventures
**Domain:** educational technology / learning management systems
**Website:** https://www.instructure.com

## Overview
Instructure is an educational technology company that develops and markets the Canvas learning management system (LMS). Canvas is used by K–12 schools, higher education institutions, and corporate training programs worldwide. The platform is known for its open API, third-party integrations, cloud-native design, and user-friendly interface. Instructure also offers products like Mastery Connect (assessment management), Canvas Credentials (digital badging), and a data analytics platform.

Founded in 2008, Instructure went public in 2015 and was later taken private by Thoma Bravo in 2020. In 2024, the company was acquired by KKR and other investors. Today, Canvas is the dominant LMS in U.S. higher education and a leading choice for many K–12 districts, serving over 30 million users globally.

## Utah connection
Instructure was founded in Salt Lake City, Utah, and its headquarters remain in the state. The company’s growth helped shape Utah’s “Silicon Slopes” tech ecosystem, providing a major success story in edtech. Instructure’s roots in Utah have also contributed to a local talent pipeline in software engineering, product design, and education technology roles.

